						               													<description>Circus is a board game, a family filler in which you will have to find out the secret combination of circus characters. To do this you will have the help of a blackboard where you can write down everything that happens during the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the beginning of the game and randomly 5 character tokens will be placed face down on the board. Taking turns, all the people will roll the die, the number they get will be the number of tokens they will be able to flip over. That will be the first information they will have. The rest they will have to find out during the course of the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To facilitate the work there are the character cards that have their own abilities.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Track boss: you can move a card from the playing area to the discard deck.&amp;#10;     Clown: you can swap the position of two character cards on the board.&amp;#10;     Bullet woman: everyone must quickly put his hand on this card, the last one to do so must uncover a card from his playing area.&amp;#10;     Trapeze artist: swap a card from your hand with a card from an opponent's hand.&amp;#10;     Juggler: choose who must lose the next turn.&amp;#10;     Magician: secretly uncover as many character cards on the board as the result of the die.&amp;#10;     Audience: use this card to defend yourself from the effects of the trapeze artist, juggler, or ringmaster.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To win, you must not only find out the combination of characters on the board, but you must also have in your playing area the combination formed by the cards that you have had to keep during the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The following actions are available each turn:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Draw a card from the central deck and raise it to your hand.&amp;#10;     Use a card from your hand and execute one of these actions:&amp;#10;         Lower it face down to your playing area&amp;#10;         Turn the card&amp;#10;    &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The winner is the one who manages to find out the combination of characters on the board and has the generated combination in his playing area. To end the game, the person who thinks he has the winning combination must play a Carp card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
